08/11/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Ligoraq Karamelo, the former secretary general of the Human Rights Union Party (HRUP), announced on Saturday (6 November) that he and a group of followers will found a new party dedicated to the protection of human rights and freedoms. 
It will be called the Human Rights Party.
In other news Saturday, local media reported that a young NATO soldier died from injuries sustained in a construction accident. 
He reportedly was struck by a crane jib while helping to rebuild a school in Vlora. 
(ATA - 06/11/04)
